The 
\f1\b Chow Chow
\f0\b0  is a \cf3 \ul \ulc3 spitz\cf0 \ulnone -type of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dog_breed"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 dog breed}} originally from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_China"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 northern}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 China}}.The Chow Chow is a sturdily built dog, square in profile, with a broad skull and small, triangular, erect ears with rounded tips. The breed is known for a very dense {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Double_coat"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 double coat}} that is either smooth or rough. The fur is particularly thick in the neck area, giving it a distinctive {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruff_(clothing)"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 ruff}} or mane appearance. The coat may be shaded/self-red, black, blue, cinnamon/fawn, or cream.\
